------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components (downloaded at install time, NOT distributed with this
project)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

At install time, install.sh downloads two prebuilt binaries from the
gvisor-tap-vsock project and installs them as `wsl-gvproxy.exe` and `wsl-vm`:

  gvisor-tap-vsock
    https://github.com/containers/gvisor-tap-vsock
    Copyright The gvisor-tap-vsock Authors
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

    - release asset `gvproxy-windows.exe`  -> installed as wsl-gvproxy.exe
    - release asset `gvforwarder`          -> installed as wsl-vm

The `wsl-gvproxy.exe` / `wsl-vm` naming convention follows the wsl-vpnkit
project, which popularized running gvisor-tap-vsock under WSL2:

  wsl-vpnkit
    https://github.com/sakai135/wsl-vpnkit
    Copyright (c) sakai135
    Licensed under the MIT License.

These upstream binaries are obtained directly from their official releases and
are not redistributed as part of this repository.
